00:00:01.767 --> 00:00:03.700
ROB MCCLENDON: WELL
HERE IS SOMETHING
TO THINK ABOUT.

00:00:03.700 --> 00:00:06.967
WHEN IT COMES TO THE
LANGUAGE OF BUSINESS,
ENGLISH IS THE MOST WIDELY

00:00:06.967 --> 00:00:08.000
SPOKEN.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:11.633
BUT AFTER THAT IT IS NOT
JAPANESE, FRENCH OR EVEN
MANDRIN CHINESE THAT COMES

00:00:11.633 --> 00:00:13.033
IN SECOND.

00:00:13.033 --> 00:00:18.033
IT IS SPANISH, WHICH IS
WHY ONE TULSA SCHOOL IS
OFFERING A BILINGUAL

00:00:18.033 --> 00:00:19.166
EDUCATION.

00:00:19.166 --> 00:00:21.400
JOINING ME NOW IS
OUR ANDY BARTH.

00:00:21.400 --> 00:00:24.633
ANDY BARTH: WELL ROB, THE
AMERICAN WORKFORCE IS
EVOLVING ON A DAILY BASIS.

00:00:24.633 --> 00:00:28.633
IN THE NEXT TEN YEARS, AS
MANY AS EIGHTY-SEVEN
MILLION BABY BOOMERS WILL

00:00:28.633 --> 00:00:29.867
REITRE.

00:00:29.867 --> 00:00:33.333
AND AS OF NOW THERE ARE
ONLY FIFTY-SEVEN MILLION
PEOPLE READY TO REPLENISH

00:00:33.333 --> 00:00:35.266
AMERICAN JOBS.

00:00:35.266 --> 00:00:39.633
AND, A GROWING TREND IN
STATES LIKE TEXAS,
OKLAHOMA, AND KANSAS IS

00:00:39.633 --> 00:00:43.266
THAT HISPANICS ARE A
GROWING PART OF THE
WORK-READY AGE GROUP,

00:00:43.266 --> 00:00:47.533
MAKING IT NECESSARY
FOR OUR YOUNG PEOPLE
TO BECOME BILINGUAL.

00:00:47.533 --> 00:00:52.166
ANDY: AT FIRST GLANCE,
IT'S YOUR TYPICAL
ELEMENTARY SCHOOL.

00:00:52.166 --> 00:00:58.700
BUT IF YOU LISTEN
CLOSELY, THE WORDS BEING
SUNG ARE IN SPANISH.

00:00:58.700 --> 00:01:03.133
PEGGY MOSS: OUR MISSION
IS TO GROW SUCCESSFUL
GLOBAL CITIZENS.

00:01:03.133 --> 00:01:07.867
AND SO I THINK THAT
EVERYTHING WE DO WE TRY TO
TIE BACK TO THAT MISSION.

00:01:07.867 --> 00:01:15.767
ANDY: INSIDE THESE
CLASSROOMS YOU'LL HEAR AS
MUCH SPANISH AS ENGLISH.

00:01:15.767 --> 00:01:19.533
PEGGY MOSS IS THE
SCHOOL'S PRINCIPAL.

00:01:19.533 --> 00:01:24.133
MOSS: IMMERSION IS
BASICALLY LEARNING CONTENT
AND ALL OF THE OBJECTIVES

00:01:24.133 --> 00:01:26.834
AND SKILLS THAT YOU
NORMALLY WOULD IN SCHOOL
BUT THROUGH A SECOND

00:01:26.834 --> 00:01:28.200
LANGUAGE.

00:01:28.200 --> 00:01:32.600
OUR KIDS COME IN AT PRE-K
AND THEY LEARN THE SAME
CURRICULUM AS THE REST OF

00:01:32.600 --> 00:01:36.900
TULSA PUBLIC SCHOOLS,
THEY JUST LEARN
IT THROUGH SPANISH.

00:01:36.900 --> 00:01:41.033
AND IN THAT PROCESS
THEY'RE ACTUALLY LEARNING
THE SPANISH LANGUAGE.

00:01:41.033 --> 00:01:44.834
AT THIS AGE THE CHILD'S
BRAIN IS LIKE A SPONGE FOR
LANGUAGE, THEY'RE STILL

00:01:44.834 --> 00:01:47.900
LEARNING THEIR
OWN LANGUAGE.

00:01:47.900 --> 00:01:52.633
ANDY: AND IN MICHELLE
SAENZ'S KINDERGARDEN
CLASS, THE LEARNING CURVE

00:01:52.633 --> 00:01:54.967
IS SET PRETTY HIGH.

