MICHELLE SAENZ: I THINK
EVERY CHILD NEEDS TO HAVE
A SECOND LANGUAGE BECAUSE

00:01:58.567 --> 00:02:05.367
WE'RE SO DIVERSE AND ALSO
BECAUSE IT'S MORE
IMPORTANT FOR WHEN THEY'RE

00:02:05.367 --> 00:02:10.800
OLDER THEY HAVE
MORE OPPORTUNITIES
IN THE JOB MARKET.

00:02:10.800 --> 00:02:13.767
ANDY: FOR SAENZ, TEACHING
KINDERGARDEN IS A FIRST.

00:02:13.767 --> 00:02:17.400
BUT THE PAYOFF IS BIG.

00:02:17.400 --> 00:02:19.834
SAENZ: I'VE NEVER WORKED
WITH THE LITTLE ONES
BEFORE, AND I HAVE ONES

00:02:19.834 --> 00:02:22.700
THAT ARE ALREADY
COUNTING BY TENS.

00:02:22.700 --> 00:02:26.133
WORKING IN THIRD GRADE, I
DIDN'T EVEN SEE THAT UNTIL
THE END OF THIRD GRADE SO

00:02:26.133 --> 00:02:27.367
IT'S REALLY EXCITING.

00:02:27.367 --> 00:02:31.633
AND THEN I HAVE THOSE ONES
THAT ARE TRYING THEIR
HARDEST AND JUST HIT THOSE

00:02:31.633 --> 00:02:36.667
LIGHT BULB MOMENTS
WHEN THEY GET IT, AND
IT'S REALLY EXCITING.

00:02:36.667 --> 00:02:41.133
ANDY: AND FOR STUDENTS
BRISA FLORES AND KAI
LUKENBAUGH, LEARNING IN A

00:02:41.133 --> 00:02:44.533
