BRISA FLORES &amp; KAI
LUKENBAUGH: I LIKE
SPEAKING SPANISH HERE;

00:02:47.400 --> 00:02:52.667
BECAUSE WE LEARN HOW TO
SPEAK TWO LANGUAGES.

00:02:52.667 --> 00:02:56.100
I LIKE DOING THE SENTENCES
AND DOING THE CALENDAR.

00:02:56.100 --> 00:02:58.700
PEGGY MOSS: THE DUAL
IMMERSION PART IS A VERY
IMPORTANT PART OF OUR

00:02:58.700 --> 00:02:59.734
SCHOOL.

00:02:59.734 --> 00:03:03.000
IF YOU DON'T HAVE PARENTS
AT HOME WHO CAN HELP YOU
WITH YOUR HOMEWORK, IN THE

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:06.734
CLASSROOM IS WHERE THEY
HAVE TO REALLY GET THEIR
SKILLS AND STRATEGIES TO

00:03:06.734 --> 00:03:09.600
BE ABLE TO TACKLE THE
WORK THAT WE GIVE THEM.

00:03:09.600 --> 00:03:12.300
AND IT'S THE SAME FOR
THE ENGLISH SPEAKERS TOO
BECAUSE THEIR PARENTS

00:03:12.300 --> 00:03:14.967
USUALLY CAN'T HELP THEM
WITH THEIR HOMEWORK EITHER
BECAUSE THEY DON'T SPEAK

00:03:14.967 --> 00:03:16.166
SPANISH.

00:03:16.166 --> 00:03:19.800
SO THEY'RE ALL IN THE SAME
BOAT AND THEY'RE JUST
LEARNING SIDE BY SIDE, TWO

00:03:19.800 --> 00:03:24.066
DIFFERENT POPULATIONS
THAT MIGHT NOT REALLY
BE WORKING TOGETHER

00:03:24.066 --> 00:03:25.333
OTHERWISE.

00:03:25.333 --> 00:03:29.467
SO WE FIND THAT COMPONENT
OF OUR PROGRAM PROBABLY
ONE OF THE MOST IMPORTANT

00:03:29.467 --> 00:03:34.633
AND ACTUALLY DEFINING
PIECES OF OUR PROGRAM.

00:03:34.633 --> 00:03:39.400
ANDY: BRIDGING A CULTURAL
GAP WHILE CULTIVATING
TODAY'S YOUNG MINDS.

00:03:39.400 --> 00:03:45.133
ANDY: NOW WHEN THE SCHOOL
BEGAN, IT ONLY OFFERED
PRE-K AND KINDERGARTEN.

00:03:45.133 --> 00:03:48.700
